					<description><![CDATA[I agree that exercise definitely helps with depression.  I already exercise regularly, but sometimes I don&#039;t feel like exercising.  When that happens if I usually force myself to exercise anyway I always feel better and am glad I did and if I decide not to exercise I feel worse.  So I&#039;m not sure if exercise is a cure, more like a lifelong treatment.

In either case it motivates me to keep up the work, because nobody likes feeling depressed and exercise makes me feel better physically and emotionally.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I agree that exercise definitely helps with depression.  I already exercise regularly, but sometimes I don&#8217;t feel like exercising.  When that happens if I usually force myself to exercise anyway I always feel better and am glad I did and if I decide not to exercise I feel worse.  So I&#8217;m not sure if exercise is a cure, more like a lifelong treatment.</p>
<p>In either case it motivates me to keep up the work, because nobody likes feeling depressed and exercise makes me feel better physically and emotionally.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
